President Trump delivered remarks at Yokota Air Base in Japan, expressing his gratitude and admiration for the men and women of the United States military and their Japanese counterparts. He praised the alliance between the two nations and highlighted the importance of their partnership in maintaining peace and security in the region. The President also emphasized the strength and capabilities of the American Armed Forces and vowed to provide them with the necessary resources to defend the nation. He acknowledged the sacrifices made by servicemembers and their families and reaffirmed his commitment to supporting them. President Trump concluded his remarks by expressing his optimism for the future and his belief that freedom will prevail with the help of patriots like those in attendance.